page.title: 14LIFESTYLES - Gamekeeper
page.content: My{dad's a gamekeeper.}He has been a gamekeeper for{15 years.}Every year he gets between 400 and 800 {pheasants.}My dad's 'boss' is called Mrs. Ringrose-Wharton. He has{7 dogs}and one of them has had 7 pup's. The{Alsation}is used for {tracking poachers.}The{Labradors}are used for{pigeon and grouse-shooting. My dad looks after the pond next to De-Brus School and Skelton Beck. The dangers to the pheasants are poachers, foxes, weasels, and stoats. Mr. Anthony Wharton is Mrs. Ringrose-Wharton's son. He usually helps my dad in shoots. Mr. Wharton holds a{clay-pigeon shoot}every year on the castle lawns. My dad is a champion at clay shooting so I thought I might enter this year.
